[1
Date: Fri, 29 Jan 1999 14:45:10 +1000
From: Paul Prociv <p.prociv@mailbox.uq.oz.au>

Re:
>Actually, I claim to be the first case of chloroquine-resistant vivax from
>the island of Borneo. In 1956 I went there ...
Uh, oh -- I think you're going to be deluged with responses after this one!
What you had was the standard old relapsing vivax malaria, in which hepatic
hypnozoites (unknown in 1956, and always insensitive to chloroquine) simply
woke up and caused a relapse -- not the same as true chloroquine-resistance.
--
Paul Prociv, Assoc. Prof.
